2.
 Show that 
\begin_inset Formula $\parallel y-X\hat{b}\parallel^{2}=\overset{m}{\underset{i=n+1}{\sum}}\mid y_{i}^{*}\mid^{2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Let O be an orthogonal matrix such that 
\begin_inset Formula $X^{*}=OX$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $X^{*}$
\end_inset

 is an upper triangular matrix.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Further define 
\begin_inset Formula $Y^{*}=OY$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon^{*}=O\varepsilon$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Now, partition 
\begin_inset Formula $X^{*},Y^{*},\, and\,\varepsilon^{*}$
\end_inset

such that the regression equation can be rewritten as
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{c}
Y_{1}^{*}\\
Y_{2}^{*}
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{c}
X_{1}^{*}\\
0
\end{array}\right]b+\left[\begin{array}{c}
\varepsilon_{1}^{*}\\
\varepsilon_{2}^{*}
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}^{*}$
\end_inset

 contains the first n rows of 
\begin_inset Formula $X^{*}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
We now have that
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Formula $\parallel Y^{*}-X^{*}b\parallel^{2}=\parallel Y_{1}^{*}-X_{1}^{*}b\parallel^{2}+\parallel Y_{2}^{*}\parallel^{2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Now, we can choose b such that 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1}^{*}b=Y_{1}^{*}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Thus, we now have that
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Formula $\parallel Y^{*}-X^{*}b\parallel^{2}=\parallel Y_{2}^{*}\parallel^{2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Which, after a little algebra, gives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Formula $\parallel$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $Y_{2}^{*}\parallel^{2}=\left[Y_{2}^{*}\right]^{'}\left[Y_{2}^{*}\right]=\overset{m}{\underset{i=n+1}{\sum}}\mid y_{i}^{*}\mid^{2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

